    "original_goal": "Implement PWM functionality",
    "functional_behavior": "On KIT_A2G_TC387_5V_TFT, generate three independent single-ended PWM outputs on GTM TOM1 CH2/CH4/CH6 at 20 kHz, center-aligned with CMU Fxclk0, using TOM1 CH0 as timebase; route to P02.0/P02.1/P02.2; initialize duties to 25%/50%/75% and every 500 ms increase each by +10% with wrap-around from 100% to 0%; update Cpu0 WAIT_TIME to 500 ms.",
    "technical_approach": "Migrate from IfxGtm_Tom_PwmHl to the unified IfxGtm_Pwm driver. Enable GTM and CMU Fxclk0, configure IfxGtm_Pwm with TOM1 and timebase TOM1 CH0 for 20 kHz center-aligned operation, initialize three single-ended channels (2/4/6) and map pins using IfxGtm_PinMap_setTomTout with &IfxGtm_TOM1_2_TOUT12_P02_0_OUT, &IfxGtm_TOM1_4_TOUT14_P02_1_OUT, &IfxGtm_TOM1_6_TOUT16_P02_2_OUT. Start synced channels, then every 500 ms update duties via IfxGtm_Pwm_updateChannelsDutyImmediate with wrap-around."
